com.neebal.android.simplyreliable.message

Interface RedirectionCallback

  • All Superinterfaces:
    BaseCallback, Serializable

    public interface RedirectionCallback
extends BaseCallback
    Interface that represents the various callbacks that can be called at the time of receiving a response for a Message with redirection headers from the server
    Since:
    1.4
    Author:
    Neebal Technologies

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void handleRedirectionResponse(OutMessage outMessage, String redirectionUrl)
      Subclasses wishing to handle the redirection response that originates from a particular request, must write code in this method.

      e.g There may be some POST request that generates a redirection GET request in the response

      • Methods inherited from interface com.neebal.android.simplyreliable.message.BaseCallback

        handleConnectivityError, handleErrorResponse, handleMissingObjects

    • Method Detail

      • handleRedirectionResponse

        void handleRedirectionResponse(OutMessage outMessage,
                             String redirectionUrl)
        Subclasses wishing to handle the redirection response that originates from a particular request, must write code in this method.

        e.g There may be some POST request that generates a redirection GET request in the response
        Parameters:
        outMessage - the OutMessage instance for which this callback is called
        redirectionUrl - the url where the redirection should happen
